        "ratings": [
            {
                "comment": "It takes way more knowledge on a subject to explain it in a simple way, and Prof. Holloway is the perfect example of that. Her review sessions are basically \"just keep me talking for 75 minutes\", and she is such a wealth of knowledge that it works. She told the class that any of us would be prepared for a job in air quality and means it. ",
                "difficulty_rating": 5,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Prof. Holloway is an incredible scientist and it was a privilege to take her Air Quality class. It was definitely a difficult class and I had to work hard to pass, but I learned so much. She is extremely professional but also very supportive and invested in student success. She always answered my emails promptly.",
                "difficulty_rating": 4,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Tracey is a genius there is no denying that. She knows the material better than arguably anyone in the world which is a good and bad thing. The class takes up A LOT of time but it is not that hard. The exams are short answer and the papers due throughout the semester require some work and a lot of research. I learned a lot, though.",
                "difficulty_rating": 4,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "Tracey was a real treat. She is one the most respected professors on campus and is brilliant, however she is terribly unorganized. That is ok though because the class is terribly easy and I will miss her ramblings as you can really learn alot from her. She also cares about energy so much, she makes you want to care too",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "I loved listening to Prof. Holloway lecture because she clearly cared a lot about the class. I found that the homework was a bit long and repetitive and the quiz answers conflicted with things that had been said in class sometimes. Other than that, I really liked the class. She was really positive and always willing to discuss things further.",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "She's great but be aware of her tricky quizes. ",
                "difficulty_rating": 4,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "Tracey is da bomb diggity. She's one of the most brilliant people in the country and knows  just about everything there is to know about air quality.  Extremely approachable, loves getting questions, responds to emails in a jiff, and cares to make sure her students understand the material. Take a class with her if you can",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            }
